4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REQUIRING A NEW SCHOOL BUS PURCHASED ON OR AFTER
5 JANUARY 1, 2026, TO BE EQUIPPED WITH LAP-SHOULDER BELTS; PROVIDING EXCEPTIONS;
6 LIMITING GOVERNMENTAL LIABILITY; CLARIFYING BID LETTING REQUIREMENTS REGARDING LAP-
7 SHOULDER BELTS IN SCHOOL BUS TRANSPORTATION CONTRACTS; REVISING SCHOOL BUS RATE
8 CAPACITY REQUIREMENTS; DECREASING CERTAIN REGISTRATION FEES FOR SCHOOL BUSES
9 EQUIPPED WITH LAP-SHOULDER BELTS; REVISING DEFINITIONS; AMENDING SECTIONS 20-10-101,
10 20-10-125, 20-10-141, 61-3-529, AND 61-9-421, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE AND AN
11 APPLICABILITY DATE.”
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
14
15 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Lap-shoulder belt requirement for school buses -- limits on liability.
16 (1) A school bus that is purchased new on or after January 1, 2026, for use in the state must be equipped with
17 lap-shoulder belts for each passenger.
18 (2) A school district that uses a school bus equipped with lap-shoulder belts shall:
19 (a) adopt an enforceable, publicly available lap-shoulder belt usage policy;
20 (b) require all passengers on the school bus to use lap-shoulder belts; and
21 (c) ensure that all lap-shoulder belts are properly maintained and in good working order.
22 (3) A person may not be charged with violating this section or any administrative rule adopted to
23 implement this section if another passenger on the school bus fails to use or improperly uses the lap-shoulder
24 belt and the school has adopted an enforceable, publicly available lap-shoulder belt usage policy.
25 (4) (a) When a school district has adopted an enforceable, publicly available lap-shoulder belt
26 usage policy, the state, the county, the school district, a school bus contractor, a school bus driver under
27 contract with the school district, or an agent or employee of the school district is not liable in an action for
28 personal injury by a school bus passenger:
